Location\",\"@id\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/joyner-park-community-center\",\"name\":\"Joyner Park Community Center\",\"url\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/joyner-park-community-center\",\"description\":\"Joyner Park Community Center has become the premier destination for Wake Forest dog owners. This facility features climate-controlled facilities for North Carolina's varied weather, North Carolina...\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"Wake Forest\",\"addressRegion\":\"NC\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"},\"image\":\"/images/parks/northcarolina/joyner-park-community-center/joyner-park-community-center-1.jpg\"}}]}</script><script type=\"application/ld+json\">{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"FAQPage\",\"mainEntity\":[{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Where is the dog park in Wake Forest?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Flaherty Dog Park is the town’s premier off-leash facility. It features two acres of shaded, grassy play space with separate areas for large and small dogs.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Are dogs allowed at Joyner Park?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Yes! E. Carroll Joyner Park is fantastic for dogs. Leashed pets can explore the 3 miles of paved trails and the expansive open meadows.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Can I walk on the Falls Lake Dam?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Yes, the dam offers a great paved walking surface with water on both sides. Dogs must be on a leash, and it can get windy!\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What are the leash rules in Wake Forest?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Wake Forest enforces Wake County animal control laws, which require dogs to be leashed at all times in public parks and greenways.\"}}]}</script><script type=\"application/ld+json\">{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BreadcrumbList\",\"itemListElement\":[{\"@type\":\"Li